		<td><b>Why didn't CRTs use colored light beams?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Is there a reason why CRTs typically used white beams of light and had to rely on a shadow mask to separate the colors, and the phosphors to do the coloring?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
