	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sort of. Not in the way you're thinking, where the <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NJbGVEfDbwY" class="postlink">mirrors completely recapitulate the deflection coils</a> of a conventional CRT.<br /><br />Modern &quot;laser&quot; projectors often use the LASER diode (and/or diodes) to get a very narrow-band light source for higher energy efficiency and better gamut, and then reflect that light off a DLP array (and all of the pixels in that are, in fact, mirrors)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


